modules.description: This module implements HTTP/2 client functionality for calling Twirp RPC services over CoHTTP-Lwt in a Unix environment. It provides a `call` function to invoke unary Twirp methods with configurable encoding, TLS, headers, and service prefix, returning decoded responses or structured errors. It works with standard OCaml types, Twirp-generated request/response types, and handles low-level transport details for client-server communication.
